---
description: How Cursor should work on Godot tasks in this project.
alwaysApply: true
---

Before coding:

- Read [docs/index.md](docs/index.md); design intent in `docs/design/00`–`05`.
- Read [docs/engineering/project-status.md](docs/engineering/project-status.md) — do not assume `scripts/` or `scenes/` exist until listed there.
- Use [docs/engineering/implementation-tracker.md](docs/engineering/implementation-tracker.md) for feature-level target vs built.
- Respect **Khan 1 gate** ([docs/design/00-project-index.md](docs/design/00-project-index.md) §3) unless explicitly scoped wider.
- Smallest useful change; ask only when blocked.

When coding:

- Work at **repo root** (`project.godot`); `res://` paths in scenes and resources.
- Target layout: [docs/engineering/architecture.md](docs/engineering/architecture.md).
- Stable `.tres` IDs — never display names or filename guessing in gameplay code.
- After milestones: update [docs/engineering/project-status.md](docs/engineering/project-status.md) and flip rows in [implementation-tracker.md](docs/engineering/implementation-tracker.md).
- No new paid power, battle pass, or forced ads ([docs/design/03-monetization.md](docs/design/03-monetization.md)).
- TODO comments only for real follow-up.

After coding:

- Summarize changed files.
- Test: Godot 4.6 → F5/F6 → expected behavior + edge cases.
- Note gaps vs design canon; suggest next M0–M8 step ([docs/design/04-production-roadmap.md](docs/design/04-production-roadmap.md)).

Placeholders: `art/_placeholders/` until [docs/design/01-art-phases.md](docs/design/01-art-phases.md) art lands.
